# Auto-push after changes

After completing any edit that spans more than 30 lines, stage all modified files, commit with a concise message, and push to `origin main` — without waiting for the user to ask.

Don't make any changes to the files you commit and push on your own during this process. 

Use `git add -u` to stage all tracked changes — this includes any modifications made earlier in the session that haven't been committed yet, not just the current edit. Do not stage untracked files unless the user explicitly asked for them.
